{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HPGx7UcHeo5VDdHQEaoyqs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have a complete picture. Let me summarize what's non-default:\n\n**Cluster settings (via API):** Both persistent and transient are empty `{}` — nothing was changed via the API at the cluster level.\n\n**Index settings on `audit-index`:**\n- `number_of_shards: 3` — default is 1; this is a **static** setting, cannot be changed without deleting/recreating the index\n- `number_of_replicas: 1` — this IS the ES default, no change needed\n- `routing.allocation.require.tier: hot` — **non-default**; default is no requirement; can be cleared via API\n- `routing.allocation.include._tier_preference: data_content` — while this is set by default in ES 8.x for new indices, the fact that all nodes are explicitly tagged as `tier=hot` makes this configuration non-standard for the actual cluster setup\n\n**Node attributes and ILM:** All nodes have `tier: hot` configured in their settings via the StatefulSet, and the ILM policies are all built-in defaults with no custom policies created.\n\n**Index templates:** The remaining templates are Kibana and monitoring-related, all built-in.\n\nSo the reversible changes are removing the explicit tier routing requirements from the audit index and the shard count preference, though the shard count would require deleting and recreating the index. The node tier attributes themselves need to be changed at the StatefulSet level with a rolling restart. Now I'm writing the rollback script to handle these changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4302,"cache_read_input_tokens":33964,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4302},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"de4d6e53-2933-4fe9-85d3-0397a228c20f","uuid":"fc3b80bc-851e-464d-be91-239cf14131b5","request_id":"req_011CcLF7p91GWwFcLoxtprvp"}
